psampMIB.description: The PSAMP MIB defines managed objects for packet sampling and filtering. These objects provide information about managed nodes supporting packet sampling, including packet sampling capabilities, configuration, and statistics. The PSAMP MIB module registers additional top-level OIDs for the parameter subtrees of its Selector functions in the IPFIX-SELECTOR-MIB Function sub-registry according to the procedures defined in RFC 6615. psampSampCountBasedAvail.name: psampSampCountBasedAvail
psampSampCountBasedAvail.description: This object indicates the availability of systematic count-based sampling at the managed node. A Selector may be unavailable if it is implemented but currently disabled due to, e.g., administrative reasons, lack of resources, or similar.

psampSampCountBasedParamSetTable.name: psampSampCountBasedParamSetTable
psampSampCountBasedParamSetTable.description: This table lists configurations of systematic count-based packet sampling. A parameter set describing a configuration contains two parameters: the sampling interval length and space.

psampSampCountBasedParamSetEntry.name: psampSampCountBasedParamSetEntry
psampSampCountBasedParamSetEntry.description: Defines an entry in the psampSampCountBasedParamSetTable.

psampSampCountBasedIndex.name: psampSampCountBasedIndex
psampSampCountBasedIndex.description: The index of this parameter set in the psampSampCountBasedParamSetTable. It is used in the object ipfixSelectionProcessSelectorFunction entries of the ipfixSelectionProcessTable in the IPFIX-MIB as reference to this parameter set.

psampSampCountBasedInterval.name: psampSampCountBasedInterval
psampSampCountBasedInterval.description: This object specifies the number of packets that are consecutively sampled. A value of 100 means that 100 consecutive packets are sampled.

psampSampCountBasedSpace.name: psampSampCountBasedSpace
psampSampCountBasedSpace.description: This object specifies the number of packets between two intervals specified by the object psampSampCountBasedInterval. A value of 100 means that the next interval starts 100 packets (which are not sampled) after the current psampSampCountBasedInterval is over.

psampSampTimeBasedAvail.name: psampSampTimeBasedAvail
psampSampTimeBasedAvail.description: This object indicates the availability of systematic time-based sampling at the managed node. A Selector may be unavailable if it is implemented but currently disabled due to, e.g., administrative reasons, lack of resources, or similar.

psampSampTimeBasedParamSetTable.name: psampSampTimeBasedParamSetTable
psampSampTimeBasedParamSetTable.description: This table lists configurations of systematic time-based packet sampling. A parameter set describing a configuration contains two parameters: the sampling interval length and the space.

psampSampTimeBasedParamSetEntry.name: psampSampTimeBasedParamSetEntry
psampSampTimeBasedParamSetEntry.description: Defines an entry in the psampSampTimeBasedParamSetTable.

psampSampTimeBasedIndex.name: psampSampTimeBasedIndex
psampSampTimeBasedIndex.description: The index of this parameter set in the psampSampTimeBasedParamSetTable. It is used in the object ipfixSelectionProcessSelectorFunction entries of the ipfixSelectionProcessTable in the IPFIX-MIB as reference to this parameter set.

psampSampTimeBasedInterval.name: psampSampTimeBasedInterval
psampSampTimeBasedInterval.description: This object specifies the time interval in microseconds during which all arriving packets are sampled.

psampSampTimeBasedSpace.name: psampSampTimeBasedSpace
psampSampTimeBasedSpace.description: This object specifies the time interval in microseconds between two intervals specified by the object psampSampTimeBasedInterval. A value of 100 means that the next interval starts 100 microseconds (during which no packets are sampled) after the current psampSampTimeBasedInterval is over.

psampSampRandOutOfNAvail.name: psampSampRandOutOfNAvail
psampSampRandOutOfNAvail.description: This object indicates the availability of random n-out-of-N sampling at the managed node. A Selector may be unavailable if it is implemented but currently disabled due to, e.g., administrative reasons, lack of resources, or similar.

psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetTable.name: psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetTable
psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetTable.description: This table lists configurations of random n-out-of-N sampling. A parameter set describing a configuration contains two parameters: the sampling size and the parent population.

psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetEntry.name: psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetEntry
psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetEntry.description: Defines an entry in the psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetTable.

psampSampRandOutOfNIndex.name: psampSampRandOutOfNIndex
psampSampRandOutOfNIndex.description: The index of this parameter set in the psampSampRandOutOfNParamSetTable. It is used in the object ipfixSelectionProcessSelectorFunction entries of the ipfixSelectionProcessTable in the IPFIX-MIB as reference to this parameter set.

psampSampRandOutOfNSize.name: psampSampRandOutOfNSize
psampSampRandOutOfNSize.description: This object specifies the number of elements taken from the parent Population specified in psampSampRandOutOfNPopulation.

psampSampRandOutOfNPopulation.name: psampSampRandOutOfNPopulation
psampSampRandOutOfNPopulation.description: This object specifies the number of elements in the parent Population.

psampSampUniProbAvail.name: psampSampUniProbAvail
psampSampUniProbAvail.description: This object indicates the availability of random uniform probabilistic sampling at the managed node. A Selector may be unavailable if it is implemented but currently disabled due to, e.g., administrative reasons, lack of resources, or similar.

psampSampUniProbParamSetTable.name: psampSampUniProbParamSetTable
psampSampUniProbParamSetTable.description: This table lists configurations of random probabilistic sampling. A parameter set describing a configuration contains a single parameter only: the sampling probability.

psampSampUniProbParamSetEntry.name: psampSampUniProbParamSetEntry
psampSampUniProbParamSetEntry.description: Defines an entry in the psampSampUniProbParamSetTable.

psampSampUniProbIndex.name: psampSampUniProbIndex
psampSampUniProbIndex.description: The index of this parameter set in the psampSampUniProbParamSetTable. It is used in the object ipfixSelectionProcessSelectorFunction entries of the ipfixSelectionProcessTable in the IPFIX-MIB as reference to this parameter set.

psampSampUniProbProbability.name: psampSampUniProbProbability
psampSampUniProbProbability.description: This object specifies the probability that a packet is sampled, expressed as a value between 0 and 1. The probability is equal for every packet. A value of 0 means no packet is sampled since the probability is 0. A value of 1 means all packets are sampled since the probability is 1. NaN (not a number) and infinity MUST NOT be used.

psampFiltPropMatchAvail.name: psampFiltPropMatchAvail
psampFiltPropMatchAvail.description: This object indicates the availability of property match filtering at the managed node. A Selector may be unavailable if it is implemented but currently disabled due to, e.g., administrative reasons, lack of resources, or similar.

psampFiltHashAvail.name: psampFiltHashAvail
psampFiltHashAvail.description: This object indicates the availability of hash filtering at the managed node. A Selector may be unavailable if it is implemented but currently disabled due to, e.g., administrative reasons, lack of resources, or similar.

psampFiltHashParamSetTable.name: psampFiltHashParamSetTable
psampFiltHashParamSetTable.description: This table lists configurations of hash filtering. A parameter set describing a configuration contains eight parameters describing the hash function.

psampFiltHashParamSetEntry.name: psampFiltHashParamSetEntry
psampFiltHashParamSetEntry.description: Defines an entry in the psampFiltHashParamSetTable.

psampFiltHashIndex.name: psampFiltHashIndex
psampFiltHashIndex.description: The index of this parameter set in the psampFiltHashParamSetTable. It is used in the object ipfixSelectionProcessSelectorFunction entries of the ipfixSelectionProcessTable in the IPFIX-MIB as reference to this parameter set.

psampFiltHashFunction.name: psampFiltHashFunction
psampFiltHashFunction.reference: RFC 5475 (Section 6.2 and Appendixes A.1 and A.2) and RFC 1141
psampFiltHashFunction.description: The hash function used by this filter. The PSAMP-MIB defines the following hash functions: crc32(1): The CRC-32 Hash Function as defined in RFC 1141. ipsx(2): The IPSX Hash Function as described in RFC 5475, Appendix A.1. bob(3): The BOB Hash Function as described in RFC 5475, Appendix A.2.

psampFiltHashInitializerValue.name: psampFiltHashInitializerValue
psampFiltHashInitializerValue.description: This object specifies the initializer value to the hash function.

psampFiltHashIpPayloadOffset.name: psampFiltHashIpPayloadOffset
psampFiltHashIpPayloadOffset.description: This object specifies the IP payload offset used by a Hash-based Selection Selector.

psampFiltHashIpPayloadSize.name: psampFiltHashIpPayloadSize
psampFiltHashIpPayloadSize.description: This object specifies the IP payload size used by a Hash-based Selection Selector.

psampFiltHashSelectedRangeMin.name: psampFiltHashSelectedRangeMin
psampFiltHashSelectedRangeMin.description: This object specifies the value for the beginning of a hash function's selected range.

psampFiltHashSelectedRangeMax.name: psampFiltHashSelectedRangeMax
psampFiltHashSelectedRangeMax.description: This object specifies the value for the end of a hash function's selected range.

psampFiltHashOutputRangeMin.name: psampFiltHashOutputRangeMin
psampFiltHashOutputRangeMin.description: This object specifies the value for the beginning of a hash function's potential output range.

psampFiltHashOutputRangeMax.name: psampFiltHashOutputRangeMax
psampFiltHashOutputRangeMax.description: This object specifies the value for the end of a hash function's potential output range.

psampCompliance.name: psampCompliance
psampCompliance.description: The implementation of all objects is optional and depends on the implementation of the corresponding functionality in the equipment.

psampGroupSampCountBased.name: psampGroupSampCountBased
psampGroupSampCountBased.description: These objects are needed if count based sampling is implemented.

psampGroupSampTimeBased.name: psampGroupSampTimeBased
psampGroupSampTimeBased.description: These objects are needed if time based sampling is implemented.

psampGroupSampRandOutOfN.name: psampGroupSampRandOutOfN
psampGroupSampRandOutOfN.description: These objects are needed if random n-out-of-N sampling is implemented.

psampGroupSampUniProb.name: psampGroupSampUniProb
psampGroupSampUniProb.description: These objects are needed if uniform probabilistic sampling is implemented.

psampGroupFiltPropMatch.name: psampGroupFiltPropMatch
psampGroupFiltPropMatch.description: These objects are needed if property match filtering is implemented.

psampGroupFiltHash.name: psampGroupFiltHash
psampGroupFiltHash.description: These objects are needed if hash filtering is implemented.
